    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="404"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Jackson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 20, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1091.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    telegram of the 18th instant, as follows:<note n="1" xml:id="d404fn1">Printed in
                        No. 1364.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The German reply to Chinese proposals appears to be substantially on lines
                    coincident with those traced in my replies of August 12 and 16 to Minister Wu,
                    of which additional copies are inclosed. The emergency having arisen and been
                    decided by the commanders at Pekin August 15, it may be assumed that they have
                    acted under similar instructions from their Governments.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
